  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Myanmar: Strengthening Prevention and Accountability for Sexual and Gender-Based Violence (SGBV) - Phase II</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To improve knowledge and skills of formal justice actors in conflict-affected areas to investigate and prosecute cases of SGBV atrocities. 2) To better prepare community members in conflict-affected areas to identify and report SGBV cases to justice actors. 3) To increase Kachin informal justice actors&apos; knowledge and coordination with formal justice actors on early warnings and justice sector response to SGBV cases in line with international best practices.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Direct beneficiaries: Police and law officers, community members (customary and ethnic leaders, religious leaders, women leaders, representatives of community based-organizations and civil society organizations). 
Indirect beneficiaries: women and girls, as well as members of the community</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to increase prevention and accountability for sexual and gender-based violence (SGBV), including those committed as part of atrocities in conflict-affected areas in Myanmar</narrative>
  </description>
